r</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 7:45:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Proving you've done a quest when it poofs....?</span><hr size=1> I was reading another thread on this board where someone mentioned that they were doing their epic a SECOND time because one or two of the stones poofed when they turned in components to one or another mob.<br>
<br>
When I'm finished and ready to turn in the components for my epic, is there any way to prove it so that if it "poofs" they GM's will help?<br>
<br>
Does the /log on function also keep track of items turned in? Would a screen shot prove anything?<br>
<br>
Plendil <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubaragon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baragon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.cinci.rr.com/trouse/images/sword.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 4:41:13 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.cinci.rr.com/trouse/baragon/mistwalker.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proving you've done a quest when it poofs....?</span><hr size=1> Petition a GM, ask him/her to be present when you turn in the items. That's about the only proof they will accept, I believe. <p>Baragon Mistwalker<BR>
57th Preserver of Saryrn<BR>
Officer, Ancient Council<BR>
Druid Class Advisor<BR>
<img src=http://home.cinci.rr.com/trouse/misc/60hit.jpg >
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleandrasilvertongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leandra Silvertongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 5:18:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proving you've done a quest when it poofs....?</span><hr size=1> I can tell you right now that Verant is not being very helpful in this matter.  My husband is a level 60 Bard and he completed his epic, turned in all his items and got squat.  He petitioned, was told to email some guy, and he did.  Emails went back and forth - this guy basically told him &quot;sorry, your problem&quot; End result? Verant did nothing and he is having to re-do his epic from scratch (since he lost all the items as well).  Even though several other bards said that the same thing happened to them, VI is sitll unwilling to call it a *bug*... /sigh<br>
<br>
Another friend of mine, cleric - fought Ragefire and the corpse poofed on him as soon as it died.  He petitoned and he too got squat. I would not rely on Verant too much these days - they don't really seem to care too much =/ <p><BR> Leandra  Silvertongue - Druid, 56  <BR> Proud member of <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/belysium55949>Elysium</a>  <BR>  <b>"Have you hugged a Druid today? =)" </b> <BR>
