<br>
Does the /log function give enough proof for VI to reimburse if an epic quest goes bad?<br>
<br>
Plendil <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeryl>Aeryl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 7:34:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Two suggestions</span><hr size=1> When a quest fails (1) get a screenshot of text when items are given and (2) /report yourself, followed up by /petition.<br>
<br>
There is still no guarantee you will get help, but it's best way to document what you did. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueyeds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyeds</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 10:31:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two suggestions</span><hr size=1> I was told by a GM that they do not give you Epic quest items back if something goes wrong.  With other quest they are more forgiving but epics do it right the first time and Hope its not bugged.  I have seen 2 epic quests go bad Monk and Cleric.  Neither got there item restored. Both had log turned on.  The Cleric lost his when a certain druid (/hide) went LD and got the kill. <p>Eyed
Eclipse of Norrath
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarinyasinsemilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarinya Sinsemilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 6:38:12 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.aim.fr/gdl/pics/eq/Jarinya.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two suggestions</span><hr size=1> 1. When you do a /report, the content of your chat window is sent to GMs. So all you have to do is scroll your window showing the bug and do a /report.<br>
<br>
2. GMs said that they would IN NO WAY help people with epic quests. Even when it was bugged to death (with Venril remains), they didnt even talk about it and all their answers were &quot;sorry, cant help you&quot;<br>
